    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- PROJECT OVERVIEW -->
  <section>
    <h2>Project Overview</h2>
    <div class="content">
      <p>
        This project visualizes and analyzes key demographic variables for New York City using U.S. Census data. 
        The focus is on understanding spatial patterns in age distribution, income levels, and educational attainment.
      </p>
      <p>
        GIS tools such as ArcGIS and QGIS were used to create thematic maps that highlight demographic variation across neighborhoods and boroughs. 
        These visualizations support data-driven insights into social and economic trends within NYC.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

